Introduction: The Government has issued a comprehensive sand policy for the mining, storage and sale of sand / sand through online system. It was under consideration of the Government to provide funds as per the provisions of the rules for mining of sand from the river / basin, transportation to the depots, construction and management of depots as per the quantity of sand sold online by the minimum bidder till date 15.02.2024 in the tender floated at the level of Collector.
The Government's Decision-

As per the provisions of the Government Decision dated 19.04.2023, taking into account the minimum rate mentioned in the tender by the tenderer for sand quarrying, transportation and depot construction, the quantity of sand sold out of the sand excavated by the tenderers and stored in the sand depot, the amount payable to the below mentioned depot manufacturer / tenderer is as follows: -

02. The total amount to be disbursed to the Depot under the above plaque is being approved to be paid subject to the following terms and conditions: - (i) The Collector shall ensure that the amount has not been paid to the tenderers earlier.
(2) The Collector shall ensure that not more than 90 per cent of the quantity of sand sold by the tenderer is paid while spending the funds on the tree approved and received under this order.

3) The concerned should ensure that the sanctioned funds are not spent on works other than those sanctioned by the government.

4) The concerned shall ensure that no funds remain under the head account mentioned in the said order or the funds received under the said order are not deposited in any 0081811019 Bank Account / PLA (Personal Account) of the concerned authority.

5) The expenditure reports in this regard shall be submitted to the Government without fail. The expenditure reconciliation statements relating to the above funds should be submitted to the Government without fail along with the 3600700 | 8101 8 | 0 of the Accountant General's Office.

6) The utilization certificate of the funds disbursed under this order 50) The certificate should be submitted immediately to the Accountant General's Office, the concerned Collector / Divisional Commissioner / Zasnara.

7) The Collector who has earlier provided the amount to the tenderers from the District Mineral Establishment Fund for the said sand depot shall transfer the amount to the District Mineral Establishment.
The Collector will be responsible.

8) The Drawing and Disbursing Officer shall take note of the fact that any expenditure from the District Mineral Establishment Fund in excess of the amount mentioned in the Reminder by the Depot shall be treated as financial irregularity and disciplinary action shall be taken.
9) Funds from the District Mineral Establishment Fund should not be released to the depot tender holder without government approval.
